  "doc_id": "49044",
  "text": "Transthyretin is a negative acute phase reactant in humans with decreased synthesis in inflammation and stress, and its concentrations are routinely measured as an indicator of health status [CITATION_1] . In pigs, following Streptococcus suis type 2 infection transthyretin showed a negative acute phase response with serum concentrations significantly lower at two days following infection (Campbell et al. 2005) . However, its pathophysiology has not been fully elucidated in cattle.",
